                <h3>1.Natural Causes:</h3>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">Lightning:</span> Lightning strikes, particularly from dry thunderstorms, are a major 
                    natural cause of wildfires. These strikes can ignite dry vegetation, especially in 
                    forested and grassland areas.</h4>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">Volcano Eruption:</span> When a volcano erupts, it can produce lava flows and 
                        pyroclastic flows that ignite surrounding vegetation, leading to wildfires.
                </h4><br>
                <h3>2.Human Activities:</h3>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">Unattended Campfires:</span> Campfires that are not properly extinguished can 
                        reignite and spread to nearby vegetation. This is a common cause in recreational 
                        areas.</h4>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">Discarded Cigarettes:</span>Cigarettes that are carelessly discarded can easily ignite 
                        dry grass and leaves, especially during dry conditions</h4>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">Arson:</span>: Intentional setting of fires for malicious purposes or personal gain. This is 
                        a significant cause of wildfires in many regions.</h4>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">Agricultural Practices:</span>Techniques like slash-and-burn agriculture, where land 
                        is cleared by burning vegetation, can sometimes get out of control and cause 
                        wildfires.</h4><br>
                <h3>3.Environmental Factors:
                </h3>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">Drought:</span> Extended periods of dry weather can dry out vegetation, making it 
                    highly flammable and susceptible to ignition.
                </h4>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">High Winds:</span> Winds can carry embers over long distances, spreading fires 
                    rapidly and making them harder to control.                    
                </h4>
                <h4><span style="font-weight: 700; color: #48CFFB;">Heatwaves:</span> Prolonged heatwaves can dry out vegetation and increase the 
                    likelihood of wildfires.                    
                </h4><br>
                
